The `IsSome` inductive type only has one constructor `of_some` which applies to `some a` for some value `a`. Since `none` is not of the form `some a`, there's no way to construct a proof of `IsSome none`. Therefore, assuming `IsSome none` leads to a contradiction.

The proof can be done by introducing the hypothesis and then doing case analysis on it, which will have no cases since `IsSome.of_some` only applies to `some a`, not `none`.

